From 6e410e10c74858c103ec0523cb076a2e07463b92 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Arun Vikas T <vikast@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Thu, 10 Jul 2025 00:12:39 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL:wifi:nl80211: Introduce QoS Management
 command  and attributes

Add a new nl80211 command, NL80211_CMD_QOS_MGMT, to support QoS Management
(QM) operations for stations. Enable userspace to configure and receive
status updates related to QoS features.

Introduce a new nested attribute, NL80211_ATTR_QOS_MGMT, to carry
QoS Management data. Use the structured policy nl80211_qm_policy to
validate and parse the following sub-attributes:

- NL80211_QM_ATTR_MAC_ADDR: Target station MAC address (6 bytes)
- NL80211_QM_ATTR_QM_TYPE: Type of QoS Management operation (u8)
- NL80211_QM_ATTR_DIALOG_TOKEN: Dialog token for transaction tracking (u8)
- NL80211_QM_ATTR_DESCRIPTOR_PARAMS: Nested array of QoS descriptors

Validate each descriptor in NL80211_QM_ATTR_DESCRIPTOR_PARAMS using
nl80211_qm_desc_params_policy, which includes:
- QM ID, request type, priority
- TCLAS elements
- TCLAS Processing element
- QoS-specific attributes (via nl80211_qm_qos_policy)
- Status code indicating result of the operation

This framework enables fine-grained control and extensibility for QoS
Management features (SCS, MSCS) in wireless drivers and userspace tools.

Attribute structure:
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
NL80211_ATTR_QOS_MGMT [NESTED]
 ├── NL80211_QM_ATTR_MAC_ADDR
 ├── NL80211_QM_ATTR_QM_TYPE (SCS or MSCS)
 ├── NL80211_QM_ATTR_DIALOG_TOKEN
 ├── NL80211_QM_ATTR_DESCRIPTOR_PARAMS [NESTED ARRAY]
 │    ├── Desc[0] [NESTED]
 │    │    ├── NL80211_QM_DESC_ATTR_QM_ID
 │    │    ├── NL80211_QM_DESC_ATTR_REQUEST_TYPE
 │    │    ├── NL80211_QM_DESC_ATTR_PRIORITY
 │    │    ├── NL80211_QM_DESC_ATTR_TCLAS_ELEMENTS [NESTED ARRAY]
 │    │    │    ├── TCLAS[0] [NESTED]
 │    │    │    │    ├── NL80211_TCLAS_ATTR_USER_PRIORITY
 │    │    │    │    ├── NL80211_TCLAS_ATTR_CLASSIFIER_TYPE
 │    │    │    │    ├── NL80211_TCLAS_ATTR_TYPE4_PARAMS [NESTED]
 │    │    │    │    │    ├── NL80211_TCLAS_TYPE4_ATTR_CLASSIFIER_MASK
 │    │    │    │    │    ├── NL80211_TCLAS_TYPE4_ATTR_IP_VERSION
 │    │    │    │    │    ├── NL80211_TCLAS_TYPE4_ATTR_SRC_IP
 │    │    │    │    │    ├── NL80211_TCLAS_TYPE4_ATTR_DST_IP
 │    │    │    │    │    ├── NL80211_TCLAS_TYPE4_ATTR_SRC_PORT
 │    │    │    │    │    ├── NL80211_TCLAS_TYPE4_ATTR_DST_PORT
 │    │    │    │    │    ├── NL80211_TCLAS_TYPE4_ATTR_DSCP
 │    │    │    │    │    ├── NL80211_TCLAS_TYPE4_ATTR_PROTOCOL
 │    │    │    │    │    ├── NL80211_TCLAS_TYPE4_ATTR_FLOW_LABEL
 │    │    │    │    ├── NL80211_TCLAS_ATTR_TYPE10_PARAMS [NESTED]
 │    │    │    │    │    ├── NL80211_TCLAS_TYPE10_ATTR_PROT_INSTANCE
 │    │    │    │    │    ├── NL80211_TCLAS_TYPE10_ATTR_PROT_NUMBER
 │    │    │    │    │    ├── NL80211_TCLAS_TYPE10_ATTR_FILTER_VALUE
 │    │    │    │    │    ├── NL80211_TCLAS_TYPE10_ATTR_FILTER_MASK
 │    │    │    ├── TCLAS[1] [NESTED]
 │    │    ├── NL80211_QM_DESC_ATTR_TCLAS_PROCESSING
 │    │    ├── NL80211_QM_DESC_ATTR_QOS_ATTRIBUTES [NESTED]
 │    │    │    ├── NL80211_QM_QOS_ATTR_CONTROL_INFO
 │    │    │    ├── NL80211_QM_QOS_ATTR_MIN_SVC_INTERVAL
 │    │    │    ├── NL80211_QM_QOS_ATTR_MAX_SVC_INTERVAL
 │    │    │    ├── NL80211_QM_QOS_ATTR_MIN_DATA_RATE
 │    │    │    ├── NL80211_QM_QOS_ATTR_DELAY_BOUND
 │    │    │    ├── NL80211_QM_QOS_ATTR_MAX_MSDU_SIZE
 │    │    │    ├── NL80211_QM_QOS_ATTR_SVC_START_TIME
 │    │    │    ├── NL80211_QM_QOS_ATTR_SVC_START_TIME_LINK_ID
 │    │    │    ├── NL80211_QM_QOS_ATTR_BURST_SIZE
 │    │    │    ├── NL80211_QM_QOS_ATTR_MSDU_LIFETIME
 │    │    │    ├── NL80211_QM_QOS_ATTR_MSDU_DELIVERY_INFO
 │    │    │    ├── NL80211_QM_QOS_ATTR_MEDIUM_TIME
 │    │    ├── NL80211_QM_DESC_ATTR_STATUS
 │    ├── Desc[1] [NESTED]
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

